long_desc.thetext:
Your package gpick failed to build from source in current rawhide.
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17719237
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_26_Mass_Rebuild

It looks like a regression from other architectures compared to the last mass build: https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/buildinfo?buildID=772879 . I added offensive arches as blocker and currently build with the latest upstream snapshot.

Scratch result with latest snapshot: https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17927868
It looks like a bug on gcc-c++ with other arches. i686 and x86_64 successfully built.

(In reply to Luya Tshimbalanga from comment #5) > Scratch result with latest snapshot: > https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17927868 > > It looks like a bug on gcc-c++ with other arches. i686 and x86_64 > successfully built.
It's not a gcc bug, it's broken ragel (incorrect use of char type), see bug 1402577 for some discussion. The workaround can be adding -fsigned-char to CFLAGS.
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.
This package appears to have been rebuilt for fc26 - Closing.
